fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_axes([0,0,1,1])
labels = df["Mode_Production"].value_counts().index
x = np.arange(len(labels))  # the label locations
space = 0.25  # the width of the bars
y = df_cleaned["Mode_Production"].value_counts()
z = df_EAS_1["Mode_Production"].value_counts()
ax.bar(x - space/2 , y, color = 'steelblue', width = 0.25, align='center')
ax.bar(x + space/2, z, color = 'mediumaquamarine', width = 0.25, align='center')
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(labels)
plt.xlabel('EAS_1 - Mode Production', fontweight='bold');

z1 = df_EAS_1["Mode_Production"].value_counts().sort_index()

z3 = df_EAS_3["Mode_Production"].value_counts().sort_index()
z4 = df_EAS_4["Mode_Production"].value_counts().sort_index()
 
# Set position of bar on X axis
r1 = [1,4,7,10]
r2 = [x + barWidth for x in r1]
r3 = [x + barWidth for x in r2]
r4 = [x + barWidth for x in r3]
r5 = [x + barWidth for x in r4]
r6 = [x + barWidth for x in r5]

# Make the plot
ax.bar(r2, y, color='#7f6d5f', width=barWidth, edgecolor='white', label='POP')
ax.bar(r3, z1, color='darkgreen', width=barWidth, edgecolor='white', label='EAS_1')
ax.bar(r4, z2, color='forestgreen', width=barWidth, edgecolor='white', label='EAS_2')
ax.bar(r5, z3, color='limegreen', width=barWidth, edgecolor='white', label='EAS_3')
ax.bar(r6, z4, color='mediumspringgreen', width=barWidth, edgecolor='white', label='EAS_4')
 
# Add xticks on the middle of the group bars
plt.xlabel('EAS - Mode Production', fontweight='bold')
plt.xticks(r4, y)

# X axis labels
labels = df["Mode_Production"].value_counts().index
ax.set_xticklabels(labels)

def f(a,b):
    V=[]
    for i in range(1,201):
        c=math.ceil(b+(a*i))-1
        V.append(c)

def systematic_sampling(df, step):
    
    indexes = np.arange(0,len(df),step=step)
    systematic_sample = df.iloc[indexes]
    return systematic_sample

def systematic_sampling(df, step):
    
    indexes = np.arange(0,len(df),step=step)
    systematic_sample = df.iloc[indexes]
    return systematic_sample

Allocation proportionnelle
$$ \begin{aligned} \large n_{h} = n \frac{C_{h} X_h^q}{\sum_{h}C_{h} X_h^q} \; \small avec \;\; q=\frac{1}{2} \;\; et \;\; C_{h}=\frac{S_{h}}{\bar{Y_{h}}} \end{aligned} $$

df_ESR1=df_cleaned.loc[df_cleaned['Superficie_Champ'] < median]
df_ESR2=df_cleaned.loc[df_cleaned['Superficie_Champ'] >= median]
n=200
C1=np.std(df_ESR1["Superficie_Champ"])/np.mean(df_ESR1["Superficie_Champ"])
C2=np.std(df_ESR2["Superficie_Champ"])/np.mean(df_ESR2["Superficie_Champ"])
Xq1=(np.median(df_ESR1["Superficie_Champ"]))**0.5
Xq2=(np.median(df_ESR2["Superficie_Champ"]))**0.5

Nh1=n*((C1*Xq1)/(C1*Xq1+C2*Xq2))
Nh2=n*((C2*Xq2)/(C1*Xq1+C2*Xq2))
print('measure of size = mediane')
print('Nh1= ',round(Nh1))
print('Nh2= ',round(Nh2))
